  <description type="morphology">Annuals (sometimes perennials in S. frondosum); taprooted. Stems usually branched.
    Heads radiate or disciform. Ray (or pistillate) florets more numerous than disc florets, in 2–5+
    series (corollas reduced to narrow laminae or to tubes). Disc corollas barely ampliate, lobes
    erect. Pappi longer than disc florets at flowering. x = 7.</description>
  <description type="distribution">North America</description>
